latestPosts.caption:
Feeling incredibly grateful and humbled as I share this milestone moment with you all – I just received my first award as an actor for my role in *Naate* at the Jaipur International Film Festival! 🌟 The journey began with the award ceremony on the first day, followed by a wonderful few days where all the selected films were premiered. It was inspiring to witness so many amazing stories being shared and celebrated. “Luck is what happens when preparation meets opportunity,” and this recognition feels like the perfect blend of hard work and timing. 

A huge congratulations to everyone whose films were premiered at the festival – your talent and passion truly shine! I’m thankful to the universe for bringing me on this beautiful journey, to my amazing team for their unwavering support, and to the audience for their love. Here’s to more stories, more growth, and more incredible cinema ahead! Keep pushing, keep dreaming, and keep believing! 🙏 #Grateful #Milestone #ActorLife #Naate #JaipurInternationalFilmFestival #Congratulations#casting #castingdirectors #jiff #jaipur #jaipurfestival #filmfestival #bestactor #award 

Director @shyyamupadhyay

latestPosts.caption:
I get so emotional remembering this day — performing at @prithvitheatre had always been a dream of mine, ever since I watched so many incredible and talented actors grace that stage.

Finally, my very first performance at *Prithvi Theatre* in *Ali Baba and Forty Thieves* — a truly unforgettable moment!

Huge shoutout to our amazing director, @sahilvaid24 👏👏👏

I’m beyond grateful to you, Sahil sir , for trusting me and giving me this opportunity.

One of the most exciting parts was getting to play two different characters in our two shows — such a rewarding challenge!

Special thanks to our incredible backstage team and my talented co-actors — you all made this journey even more special.

Here’s to keeping the spirit of theatre alive, together! 🎭

Ps : Special thanks to all my near and dear ones, family and friends who came to watch my play and made it even more special for me, thank you for all your support. 

.
.
.
